<span id="freeTextContainer15519779102215001600">Even better than I remember. My grandfather Breyer was a big Civil War buff and this is one of his books that I inherited along the way. It has been a while since I had read it and it was even better than I remembered. Mr. Catton makes the history of the Army of the Potomac campaign through the spring and summer of 1862 come alive while at the same time bringing focus on the larger military and political issues that influenced that campaign. I was also impressed in the subtle ways he made his po</span>
  <span id="freeText15519779102215001600" style="display:none">Even better than I remember. My grandfather Breyer was a big Civil War buff and this is one of his books that I inherited along the way. It has been a while since I had read it and it was even better than I remembered. Mr. Catton makes the history of the Army of the Potomac campaign through the spring and summer of 1862 come alive while at the same time bringing focus on the larger military and political issues that influenced that campaign. I was also impressed in the subtle ways he made his points avoiding the sledgehammer that too many writers use today. Highly recommended for any reader but you will derive even more pleasure from the book if you already know some of the history. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15519779102215001600" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

