<span id="freeTextContainer17526863045635725736">Pretty good. I&apos;ve read some Civil War history before. Not sure exactly what, except definitely McPherson. Anyway, after a few books I bought one called &quot;Antietem&quot; and I thought I was ready for a one-battle book, but I was not and I did not finish it. This thing is 3 volumes for the army of the potomac. This subject is perhaps 1/3rd or 1/5th of the &quot;full war&quot; in some imprecise and uninformed guess. It moves along pretty well.<br/><br/>Lots of really flowery and poetic writing by the author. Possibly inspir</span>
  <span id="freeText17526863045635725736" style="display:none">Pretty good. I've read some Civil War history before. Not sure exactly what, except definitely McPherson. Anyway, after a few books I bought one called "Antietem" and I thought I was ready for a one-battle book, but I was not and I did not finish it. This thing is 3 volumes for the army of the potomac. This subject is perhaps 1/3rd or 1/5th of the "full war" in some imprecise and uninformed guess. It moves along pretty well.<br /><br />Lots of really flowery and poetic writing by the author. Possibly inspired by the many banging quotes from witness accounts.</span>
