<div id="review_3366888094" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3366888094" />
    <a title="Linda Patiño" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1318877-linda-pati-o"><img alt="Linda Patiño" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1537814537p2/1318877.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3366888094?book_show_action=true">Jun 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linda Patiño" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linda Patiño" href="/user/show/1318877-linda-pati-o">Linda Patiño</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3366888094" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6828009746501825227">I had a personal interest in the leaders of the Union army in the Civil War. More specifically, documented differences of the leaders, their leadership, and the consequences. I considered this easy to read and engaging, because of Catton’s focus on the story and stories of the characters. You do not have to love history, or the Civil War, to enjoy these works.<br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

